Movie: Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny
Review: The worst part is that Harrison Ford & crew give good performances and show chemistry, there are even interesting ideas whispered at by the script! There are many hints that a better movie could have been made. Instead, this movie is dragged down by an overly-optimistic reliance on CG and, what feels like, an active rejection of pacing.
Bro the waterfall was going backwards as the boat “left” the shore
I was struck by how little “information” was ever on the screen, yet how I never felt like things were sparsely animated.
End of an era. Sincere with solid voice acting throughout. Tons of little plot pay-offs. Beautiful design.
I think this movie would be good if it was 23 minutes long
Love how everything about this movie is pretty straight down the middle standard, but then Amish

Movie: Chicken Run: Dawn of the Nugget
Review: There’s that saying that goes something like, “Judge a society by how it treats the disenfranchised.” For kid’s movies, I think you can learn a lot but how it portrays the “dumb” characters.
